         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Notes on a specimen of Styphelia from Brown Mountain, Port Arthur, ¶  compared with Styphelia collina ¶  ¶ I have made a very careful examination of the specimen which you regard as S. collina and beg...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">93.00.00a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Bufton</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne. </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Annotated '1893' in an unknown hand; the annotation may not be contemporary with the letter. The date corresponds, however, to the collection <seg style="">date of </seg>MEL <seg style="">2102424, a Bufton specimen from Port Arthur</seg>, <seg style="">filed under </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leucopogon ericoides </seg>
                     <seg style="">— a genus that M felt could not be maintained — and the letter is dated accordingly.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Notes on a specimen of Styphelia from Brown Mountain, Port Arthur,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Tas.</p>
               </note> compared with <name key="Styphelia%20collina">Styphelia collina</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have made a very careful examination of the specimen which you regard as S. collina and beg to submit result for your kind consideration.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The plant has a sturdy growth being stiff and woody in stem, height about 18 inches; bushy.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Leaf</hi>
               </seg> broadly-ovate, scarcely pointed, glabrous and shining above, thick, flat, very <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">distinctly ribbed</hi>
               </seg> with 6 or 7 ribs or venules, all the lateral ones divided or bifurcated making 12-14 at margin, which is quite entire; leaves pointing upwards or nearly horizontal never lying up or down the stem.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Flower &amp; fruit</hi>
               </seg>. Very small magnifying power does not enable me to speak positively on these; but flowers are comparatively few, densely cottony.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My plant agrees much better with your description of S. costata than with S. collina, and more nearly with Mr Spicer's brief description of S. Hookeri than with S. collina.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enclose a specimen of S. collina for comparison and trust you will forgive my presumtion in requesting your further examination of the plant under consideration.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I also send specimen of <name key="Lepyrodia">Lepyrodia</name> which occurs only in one place known to me. viz on Tasman Peninsula in white sand among bushes of <name key="Melaleuca%20squarrosa">Melaleuca squarrosa</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With sincere regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours ever</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John Bufton</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
